t Order, you enter how much money you want to spend and it buys shares at any price until you have spent all the money you entered.  That can be a disaster, you can und up buying shares worth $1 for 99c even though you thought you would be buying them for 30c.\n\nIn a Limit Order, you enter how many shares you want to buy and the highest price you are willing to buy them at.  This gives you more control against getting fucked in a particular way.\n\nLimit Orders also let you save an order for cheaper than the current price, which won't buy immediately but will buy if the price ever falls that low.  You can also set these orders to expire after some amount of time.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357807,"parentCommentID":"2847328","userAddress":"0xec3811fa348a33c8be5ef8fa19dddb716ac94bce","replyAddress":"0x0caa48e58bab42cfa985fe6f4d7bf66d68e242c6","createdAt":"2026-04-26T23:37:09.2086Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-26T23:37:16.416255Z","profile":{"name":"taerv534","pseudonym":"Canine-Practice","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x30f91b6df5a62ab2e504045e25fd449a23affbfc","baseAddress":"0xec3811fa348a33c8be5ef8fa19dddb716ac94bce"},"reactions":[{"id":"2808758","commentID":2847388,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x0caa48e58bab42cfa985fe6f4d7bf66d68e242c6","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xdfb7c75fc0e19df6bf27dd47a945b5597440d958"}},{"id":"2808898","commentID":2847388,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":2},{"id":"2847447","body":"Copy paste ur orders to a google doc and set them manually again? I don't see any other quick fix sorry bro","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357807,"parentCommentID":"2847328","userAddress":"0x304f5d4eb5d3c0f1e0d843d2e9dbe64a9a0e824e","replyAddress":"0xec3811fa348a33c8be5ef8fa19dddb716ac94bce","createdAt":"2026-04-26T23:58:53.45242Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-26T23:59:05.03216